  <brief_title>Renal Denervation on Quality of 24-hr BP Control by Ultrasound In Resistant Hypertension</brief_title>
  <acronym>REQUIRE</acronym>
  <official_title>A Clinical Study of the Ultrasound Renal Denervation System in Patients With Resistant Hypertension</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>JIMRO Co., Ltd.</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>JIMRO Co., Ltd.</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The REQUIRE STUDY is a multi-center, randomized, double-blind, sham-controlled study, which
      aims to confirm the efficacy and safety of PRDS-001 (ReCor Medical Inc. Paradise® in Europe)
      for renal denervation therapy in patients with treatment resistance hypertension, in
      comparison with the sham procedure.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients with treatment resistance hypertension is defined patients being treated on 3 or
      more different classes of antihypertensive medications including diuretics.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
